    "collapsible_content_tCz3ig": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_VMEbTk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Method 1: String or Paper Strip Method",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>This is the most popular and accurate method for measuring your ring size at home. You'll need a piece of string or a thin strip of paper, a ruler and a pen.  </p><p> </p><ol><li>Cut a strip of paper about 6 inches long and 1/4 inches wide, or use a piece of string of a similar length. </li><li>Wrap the paper or string around the base of your ring finger, positioning it where the ring would normally sit.</li><li>Ensure the material is snug but not tight - it should slide over your knuckle comfortably.</li><li>Mark with a pen where the paper or string overlaps to complete the circle.</li><li>Lay the material flat and measure the length from the start to your mark using a ruler in millimetres.</li><li>Use our sizing chart below to convert your measurement to the correct ring size.</li></ol>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_zwfxWn": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Method 2: Existing Ring Measurement",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>If you have a ring that fits well on the intended finger, you<br/>can measure its internal diameter to determine your size.</p><p> </p><ol><li>Choose a ring that fits comfortably on the finger you want to size.</li><li>Place the ring on a flat surface and measure the internal diameter using a ruler.</li><li>Measure from the inside edge to the opposite inside edge, ensuring you measure the widest part.</li><li>Record your measurement in millimetres for the most accurate<br/>conversion.</li><li>Use our diameter conversion chart to find your corresponding<br/>UK ring size.</li><li>Consider that different ring styles may require slight size adjustments.</li></ol>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_EfUDtx": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Method 3: Professional Ring Sizer (Recommended)",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>For the most accurate measurement, we recommend using a professional ring sizer. We include one free with every Lily Blanche order, or you can request one from most local jewellers.</p><p> </p><p>Using a Ring Sizer:</p><ol><li>Slide the ring sizer onto your finger, starting with a smaller size.</li><li>Gradually increase the size until you find one that slides over your knuckle with slight resistance.</li><li>The correct size should feel snug but comfortable, allowing for natural finger movement.</li><li>Test the fit by making a fist - the ring should not feel uncomfortably tight.</li></ol>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_7CkCwg": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why Professional Ring Sizers Are Best",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<ul><li>Account for Knuckle size variations </li><li>Test actual ring thickness.</li><li>Provide Consistent, Standardised measurements.</li><li>Allow for comfort testing with movement.</li></ul>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
